  ],
  "subject": [],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "",
      "abstract": "Enacts the \"Terminate Excessive Cross-state Actuarial Subsidization (TEXAS) Act\" which requires life insurance companies to take state specific population health information into account as a factor; requires the superintendent of financial services to develop a standard weight to be given to state specific population health information in rate-setting."
    }
  ],
